            ...
            Student* s = new Student(name, id, roll, dept, sem, managedBy);
            s->setPresentClasses(present);
            students.push_back(s);

            if (auth != nullptr)
                auth->addStudentCredential(id, id);
```

For each student record, a new `Student` is heap-allocated and its present classes are set. Credentials are re-registered after loading because the `AuthSystem` is stored in memory only — it is not persisted to a file. Without this step, students saved to disk would not be able to log in after the program restarts.

