## 10. The `AdminMenu` Class

The `AdminMenu` is nearly identical in structure to `TeacherMenu`. The key difference is that it also manages teachers (add/remove), whereas teachers can only manage students. It also has a "File Operations" menu item that lets the admin explicitly save or load data.

The admin's `menuAddStudent()` no longer manually calls `auth.addStudentCredential()` — this was a bug that was fixed. The comment in the code even explains this: doing it manually here *and* inside `addStudent()` would register credentials twice. Since `addStudent()` now handles it internally, the admin menu simply calls `addStudent()` and trusts the method to do everything correctly.

